{"type":"text","timestamp":1775881325995,"sessionID":"ses_28539d69effe2U3nTsLsyg7mOL","part":{"id":"prt_d7ac68ac9001jPgnHijS2CPRzl","messageID":"msg_d7ac67c2a001jWNCGYg8Dv37uj","sessionID":"ses_28539d69effe2U3nTsLsyg7mOL","type":"text","text":"Now I have enough context to write the delta-spec.md for AR-032. Let me create it following the OpenSpec format used in the existing delta specs.","time":{"start":1775881325994,"end":1775881325994}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881385387,"sessionID":"ses_28539d69effe2U3nTsLsyg7mOL","part":{"id":"prt_d7ac68dac001pbLHvBaiUU2uOn","messageID":"msg_d7ac67c2a001jWNCGYg8Dv37uj","sessionID":"ses_28539d69effe2U3nTsLsyg7mOL","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_d8bdbbfdbaf2482dbe6f0f4c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/docker/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Specification — AR-032: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `docker`  \n**Language:** Dockerfile  \n**Size:** S  \n**Type:** Multi-stage Docker build for Workload Manager, Router, and picod container images\n\n**Base Specs:** deployment/spec.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-032.1: Workload Manager Dockerfile\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `docker/Dockerfile` for building the Workload Manager container image using multi-stage build with separate build and runtime stages.\n\n#### Scenario: Build stage configuration\n- **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile` is built with repository root as context\n- **WHEN** the build stage runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `golang:1.21-alpine` as builder base image\n\n#### Scenario: Go module cache optimization\n- **GIVEN** go.mod and go.sum files exist\n- **WHEN** the build stage copies dependencies\n- **THEN** it SHALL copy `go.mod` and `go.sum` first and run `go mod download` before copying source code\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager binary compilation\n- **GIVEN** source code is copied to builder\n- **WHEN** build runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile with `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o /workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager`\n\n#### Scenario: Runtime stage base image\n- **GIVEN** build stage completes\n- **WHEN** runtime stage begins\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `alpine:3.19` as minimal runtime base image\n\n#### Scenario: Non-root user creation\n- **GIVEN** runtime stage starts\n- **WHEN** image is prepared\n- **THEN** it SHALL create non-root user `apiserver` with UID 1000\n\n#### Scenario: Binary copy to runtime image\n- **GIVEN** workloadmanager binary is built\n- **WHEN** runtime stage copies artifacts\n- **THEN** it SHALL copy binary from builder stage to `/workloadmanager`\n\n#### Scenario: Container port exposure\n- **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n- **WHEN** container runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL expose port 8080\n\n#### Scenario: Default command configuration\n- **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n- **WHEN** container starts without override\n- **THEN** it SHALL run `/workloadmanager` as entrypoint\n\n---\n\n### REQ-032.2: Router Dockerfile\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `docker/Dockerfile.router` for building the Router container image using multi-stage build with separate build and runtime stages.\n\n#### Scenario: Build stage configuration\n- **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile.router` is built with repository root as context\n- **WHEN** the build stage runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `golang:1.21-alpine` as builder base image\n\n#### Scenario: Go module cache optimization\n- **GIVEN** go.mod and go.sum files exist\n- **WHEN** the build stage copies dependencies\n- **THEN** it SHALL copy `go.mod` and `go.sum` first and run `go mod download` before copying source code\n\n#### Scenario: Router binary compilation\n- **GIVEN** source code is copied to builder\n- **WHEN** build runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile with `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o /router ./cmd/router`\n\n#### Scenario: Runtime stage base image\n- **GIVEN** build stage completes\n- **WHEN** runtime stage begins\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `alpine:3.19` as minimal runtime base image\n\n#### Scenario: Non-root user creation\n- **GIVEN** runtime stage starts\n- **WHEN** image is prepared\n- **THEN** it SHALL create non-root user `router` with UID 1000\n\n#### Scenario: Binary copy to runtime image\n- **GIVEN** router binary is built\n- **WHEN** runtime stage copies artifacts\n- **THEN** it SHALL copy binary from builder stage to `/router`\n\n#### Scenario: Container port exposure\n- **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n- **WHEN** container runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL expose port 8080\n\n#### Scenario: Default command configuration\n- **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n- **WHEN** container starts without override\n- **THEN** it SHALL run `/router` as entrypoint\n\n---\n\n### REQ-032.3: Picod Dockerfile\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `docker/Dockerfile.picod` for building the picod container image using multi-stage build with separate build and runtime stages.\n\n#### Scenario: Build stage configuration\n- **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile.picod` is built with repository root as context\n- **WHEN** the build stage runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `golang:1.21-alpine` as builder base image\n\n#### Scenario: Go module cache optimization\n- **GIVEN** go.mod and go.sum files exist\n- **WHEN** the build stage copies dependencies\n- **THEN** it SHALL copy `go.mod` and `go.sum` first and run `go mod download` before copying source code\n\n#### Scenario: Picod binary compilation\n- **GIVEN** source code is copied to builder\n- **WHEN** build runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile with `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o /picod ./cmd/picod`\n\n#### Scenario: Runtime stage base image\n- **GIVEN** build stage completes\n- **WHEN** runtime stage begins\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `alpine:3.19` as minimal runtime base image\n\n#### Scenario: Non-root user creation\n- **GIVEN** runtime stage starts\n- **WHEN** image is prepared\n- **THEN** it SHALL create non-root user `picod` with UID 1000\n\n#### Scenario: Binary copy to runtime image\n- **GIVEN** picod binary is built\n- **WHEN** runtime stage copies artifacts\n- **THEN** it SHALL copy binary from builder stage to `/picod`\n\n#### Scenario: Container port exposure\n- **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n- **WHEN** container runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL expose port 8080\n\n#### Scenario: Default command configuration\n- **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n- **WHEN** container starts without override\n- **THEN** it SHALL run `/picod` as entrypoint\n\n---\n\n### REQ-032.4: Multi-stage Build Optimization\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL optimize Docker images for size and security through multi-stage build patterns.\n\n#### Scenario: Minimal runtime image\n- **GIVEN** multi-stage build completes\n- **WHEN** final image size is measured\n- **THEN** it SHALL be under 50MB for each component (Workload Manager, Router, picod)\n\n#### Scenario: No build tools in runtime\n- **GIVEN** runtime stage completes\n- **WHEN** image is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL NOT contain go compiler, git, or build dependencies\n\n#### Scenario: Static binary linkage\n- **GIVEN** CGO_ENABLED=0 is set during build\n- **WHEN** binary runs in runtime stage\n- **THEN** it SHALL have no dynamic library dependencies\n\n#### Scenario: Alpine base image\n- **GIVEN** runtime stage uses alpine:3.19\n- **WHEN** image is scanned for vulnerabilities\n- **THEN** it SHALL have minimal CVE surface compared to Debian-based images\n\n---\n\n### REQ-032.5: Security Best Practices\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement container security best practices in all Dockerfiles.\n\n#### Scenario: Non-root user execution\n- **GIVEN** container starts\n- **WHEN** process runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL run as non-root user (UID 1000)\n\n#### Scenario: Read-only filesystem compatibility\n- **GIVEN** container runs with read-only root filesystem\n- **WHEN** application needs temporary storage\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `/tmp` volume mount if needed\n\n#### Scenario: No secrets in image\n- **GIVEN** Dockerfile is built\n- **WHEN** image layers are inspected\n- **THEN** they SHALL NOT contain hardcoded credentials, tokens, or API keys\n\n#### Scenario: Minimal attack surface\n- **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n- **WHEN** shell access is attempted\n- **THEN** image MAY exclude `/bin/sh` to prevent shell injection (optional hardening)\n\n---\n\n### REQ-032.6: Build Context and .dockerignore\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL use efficient build context by excluding unnecessary files via `.dockerignore`.\n\n#### Scenario: Exclude .git directory\n- **GIVEN** `.dockerignore` exists\n- **WHEN** build context is sent to Docker daemon\n- **THEN** `.git/` directory SHALL be excluded\n\n#### Scenario: Exclude build artifacts\n- **GIVEN** `.dockerignore` exists\n- **WHEN** build context is sent\n- **THEN** `bin/`, `pkg/`, and `*_test.go` files SHALL be excluded from context\n\n#### Scenario: Exclude development files\n- **GIVEN** `.dockerignore` exists\n- **WHEN** build context is sent\n- **THEN** `.md` files (except README if needed), `.gitignore`, and editor files SHALL be excluded\n\n#### Scenario: Include only required files\n- **GIVEN** `.dockerignore` is configured\n- **WHEN** build runs\n- **THEN** context SHALL include only: `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `cmd/`, `pkg/`, and any required configs\n\n---\n\n### REQ-032.7: Makefile Integration\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for building all three Docker images.\n\n#### Scenario: Build Workload Manager image\n- **GIVEN** Makefile has `docker-build-workloadmanager` target\n- **WHEN** `make docker-build-workloadmanager` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL build image tagged `workloadmanager:latest` using `docker/Dockerfile`\n\n#### Scenario: Build Router image\n- **GIVEN** Makefile has `docker-build-router` target\n- **WHEN** `make docker-build-router` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL build image tagged `router:latest` using `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n\n#### Scenario: Build picod image\n- **GIVEN** Makefile has `docker-build-picod` target\n- **WHEN** `make docker-build-picod` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL build image tagged `picod:latest` using `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n\n#### Scenario: Build all images\n- **GIVEN** Makefile has `docker-build-all` target\n- **WHEN** `make docker-build-all` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL build all three images sequentially\n\n#### Scenario: Push Workload Manager image\n- **GIVEN** Makefile has `docker-push-workloadmanager` target with `REGISTRY` variable\n- **WHEN** `make docker-push-workloadmanager REGISTRY=registry.example.com` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL tag and push image to `registry.example.com/workloadmanager:latest`\n\n#### Scenario: Push all images\n- **GIVEN** Makefile has `docker-push-all` target with `REGISTRY` variable\n- **WHEN** `make docker-push-all REGISTRY=registry.example.com` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL tag and push all three images to specified registry\n\n---\n\n## Data Types\n\n```dockerfile\n# Docker build arguments (common to all Dockerfiles)\nARG GO_VERSION=1.21\nARG ALPINE_VERSION=3.19\nARG TARGETARCH=amd64\n\n# Labels for image metadata\nLABEL org.opencontainers.image.title=\"<component>\"\nLABEL org.opencontainers.image.description=\"AgentCube <component> component\"\nLABEL org.opencontainers.image.vendor=\"AgentCube\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\ndocker/\n├── Dockerfile           # Workload Manager image\n├── Dockerfile.router    # Router image\n├── Dockerfile.picod     # Picod image\n└── .dockerignore        # Build context exclusions (shared or per-Dockerfile)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Make Targets\n\n| Target | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `docker-build-workloadmanager` | Build Workload Manager image |\n| `docker-build-router` | Build Router image |\n| `docker-build-picod` | Build picod image |\n| `docker-build-all` | Build all three images |\n| `docker-push-workloadmanager` | Push Workload Manager image to registry |\n| `docker-push-router` | Push Router image to registry |\n| `docker-push-picod` | Push picod image to registry |\n| `docker-push-all` | Push all images to registry |\n\n---\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Component | Purpose | Default |\n|----------|-----------|---------|---------|\n| `REDIS_ADDR` | Workload Manager, Router | Redis server address | - |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Workload Manager, Router | Redis authentication | \"\" |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Router | Workload Manager endpoint | - |\n| `PORT` | All | HTTP listen port | 8080 |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Checklist\n\n- [ ] `docker/Dockerfile` — Workload Manager multi-stage build\n- [ ] `docker/Dockerfile.router` — Router multi-stage build\n- [ ] `docker/Dockerfile.picod` — Picod multi-stage build\n- [ ] `docker/.dockerignore` — Build context optimization\n- [ ] Make targets for building all three images\n- [ ] Make targets for pushing images to registry\n- [ ] Non-root user in all runtime images\n- [ ] Alpine 3.19 base for minimal image size\n- [ ] CGO disabled for static binaries\n- [ ] Port 8080 exposed in all images\n- [ ] Image size under 50MB each\n- [ ] OCI labels for image metadata\n- [ ] Go module cache optimization (go.mod copied first)\n\n---\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. Should Dockerfiles support multi-architecture builds (ARM64, AMD64) via `--platform` flag?\n2. Should health check instructions (`HEALTHCHECK`) be added to Dockerfiles?\n3. Should distroless images be used instead of Alpine for enhanced security?\n4. Should build version/commit be injected into images via `ARG` at build time?\n\n(End of file)\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/docker/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/docker/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775881385372,"end":1775881385384}}}}
